Constructor & Destructor Documentation

docAttach::docAttach ( QWidget *  parent = 0,
const char *  name = 0,
bool  modal = false,
Qt::WindowFlags  fl = 0 
)

Constructs a docAttach as a child of 'parent', with the name 'name' and widget flags set to 'f'.

The dialog will by default be modeless, unless you set 'modal' to true to construct a modal dialog.

This screen will receive the source type and id from the calling screen. Then the user will select a target type and id on this screen. When the user clicks Save, a new row will be entered into docass and the screen will return a docass_id to the calling screen.
